# 4. ヒントを探して

Shop Clerk: Here you are. Your chocolate parfait and a cup of hot tea.
Mizuki: Thanks! Oh, the parfait's mine!
Mizuki: Time to dig in! Oh, wow... It's so good♪
Kanade: It's so warm...
Mizuki: That's because you were walking around in this weather without an umbrella.
Kanade: Right. At least my clothes are starting to dry out now.
Mizuki: Thank goodness! And why don't you get something to eat, Kanade? I'll pay too since I kinda dragged you in here!
Kanade: Thanks, but I'm really not that hungry.
Mizuki: Okay... But tell me if you do, okay?
Mizuki: And isn't this place great? I love this place so much since everything on the menu's amazing and the adorable decor.
Kanade: Right...
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: So is the demo giving you a rough time...?
Kanade: It is. I haven't made much progress...
Mizuki: I see. But you don't need to feel rushed...
Kanade: The demo that I had you all listen to didn't really resonate with Mafuyu.
Kanade: So I need to finish another one for tonight.
Kanade: But I have a feeling that I'm just going to get the same result...
Mizuki: Resonate...? You won't know until you try! I think you should just have her give it a listen, you know?
Kanade: No, it's not just that. A part of me knows that it won't.
Kanade: Luka even said so. That it won't clear up what's on Mafuyu's mind.
Mizuki: Clear up what's on her mind...?
Kanade: I can't quite put my finger on it, but I think I know what Luka was trying to say. I haven't made up my mind yet, and it's why I feel so lost.
Kanade: Nothing's going to work at this rate...
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (Kanade's really in trouble, huh?)
Mizuki: (I don't know anything about songwriting...)
Mizuki: (But I want to help her in any way I can...)
Mizuki: Alright...!
Mizuki: You're really up a creek, huh? And Luka said that your song won't help Mafuyu as it is...?
Mizuki: I know! Why don't we go out and do something together?
Kanade: What? You mean right now...?
Mizuki: Yeah! You need to clear your head, right? Being cooped up at home definitely won't help, so why not get a breath of fresh air instead?
Mizuki: Who knows? You might even find something that'll help you save Mafuyu!
Kanade: I see...
Kanade: (The trip that Mizuki suggested we all go on did give us some ideas for a new song.)
Kanade: (Maybe seeing something new is the right answer in this case too...)
Kanade: (And if it means that I'll be able to compose a song that can save Mafuyu...)
Kanade: Okay... Take me somewhere.
Mizuki: Yeah, you got it!
Mizuki: But I probably should've decided on something before suggesting this...
Mizuki: Let me think... Got it! We can start with that place! Follow me, Kanade!
Kanade: O-Okay...!
Kanade: A doll store...?
Mizuki: Yeah. Remember how Mafuyu reacted when we all went to that Doll Exhibit?
Mizuki: So I thought that it might help you figure out something too!
Kanade: Oh, right...
Kanade: (But I wasn't directly responsible for that. Which means... I have to come up with something more powerful than that...)
Kanade: Hm...?
Mizuki: What's up?
Kanade: That sound... Is it a music box?
Mizuki: Yeah, I think it's this doll...
Mizuki: Oh, it plays a music box when you wind it up! That's really cute!
Kanade: Yeah, you're right. It's a nice song too...
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: Come to think of it, you include a lot of music box sounds in your songs, huh?
Mizuki: Even that last one you made. It's like you're putting your signature on each song, Kanade.
Kanade: Oh, I never thought about it like that... But I do like music boxes quite a bit.
Kanade: Especially the one my dad made. I used to listen to that one a lot.
Kanade: That might be why I'm so fascinated by them.
Mizuki: It must've been a really good song. What was it like?
Kanade: It was so gentle... Just listening to it made you feel...
Kanade: ...
Mizuki: Kanade...
Mizuki: (Did I pry too hard there...?)
Mizuki: Anyways, let's check out our next stop...!
Kanade: Uh, sure. Okay...
Mizuki: Phew... We really looked all over. How are you feeling? Tired?
Kanade: No, I feel good. It's a weekday so there aren't that many people around, but I still haven't figured anything out regarding Mafuyu...
Mizuki: Oh, yeah... I felt like that art exhibit with all those landscapes would do the trick too...
Kanade: Yes, I can see why. Mafuyu smiled when we saw those cherry blossoms so...
Mizuki: She's even been complimenting Ena's artwork too, sometimes. Maybe art's the key to getting her to feel more?
Kanade: Right. If we keep looking at artsy things, we might just...
Kanade: Oh...
Mizuki: Hm? What's up? Did that flower shop catch your eye...?
Kanade: Carnations...
Kanade: (Mom loved carnations so much...)
